http://seadas.gsfc.nasa.gov/functionality.html

SeaDAS Primary Functionalities

    1. SeaWiFS processing programs:
          + SeaWIFS L1, L2, L3, SMI (Standard Mapped Image) and Browse
            products generation
          + Level-1A to Level-0 program for renavigation
          + Ancillary quality control display program
          + Interactive L1 coastline registration and L2 QC
          + L1, L2, and L3 Binned data projection
          + L1 subscene extraction
          + coccolithophore blooms mask generation
    2. CZCS processing programs:
          + L0 to L1 processing program
          + L1 to L2 processing program
          + L1 and L2 subscene extraction
          + ringing mask generation program
          + glint mask generation program
          + coccolithophore blooms mask generation program
          + Interactive L1 and L2 coastline registration
          + Interactive L2 quality control program
    3. OCTS processing programs:
          + L0 to L1B processing program
          + L1B to L2 processing program
    4. MOS processing programs:
          + L1B destriping correction program
          + L1B to L2 processing program
    5. General display program supports:

     Input Data formats:

     All SeaWiFS data products (L0 to L3-mapped products)
     MODIS Ocean products (L1A, L1B, L2, L2A, L2B, L2 SST, L3, L4)
     OCTS L0, L1B, L2 products, L3-Binned Mapped  (NASDA format)
     OCTS L1B and L2 products (SeaDAS format)
     CZCS formats :

     SeaDAS
     DAAC HDF & PST
     SEAPAK

     MOS L1B, L2 products

     AVHRR SST/JPL PO.DAAC HDF formats:
     Pathfinder Best SST (9km, 18km & 54km)
     MCSST (18km)

     SeaDAS Mapped HDF files

     General HDF (any 2D SDs in an HDF file)

     Binary flat files

     GIF & TIFF & True Color

     Sensor-specific functions:
     Display Level-2 flags for SeaWiFS L2 products
     Display Level-2 flags for OCTS L2 products
     Display Level-2 flags for MODIS L2 products

     Navigation Functions for all navigable data input formats:
     Grid and Coastline graphics
     Projection & globe spinning
     Ship track plot and data extraction, interactive data line extraction
     Cursor location and data displaying

     General Functions for all data input formats:
     User-controlled display scaling
     Multiple frame buffers for image display
     Interactive annotation generation
     Histogram and color bar
     Color manipulation, multiple concurrent color tables, density slicing
     Cursor location and data displaying
     Image data spreadsheet for raw and/or geophysical values
     Image looping/movie
     Scatter plot/contour plot/profile plot
     Data display across multiple bands
     Bathymetry generation
     Arithmetic band functions
     X-Y shifting
     User-defined band operations
     Postscript, GIF, TIFF output image formats.
     ASCII, HDF SD and binary flat file output data formats.
